# Orbit environment variables — PLACEHOLDERS ONLY. Never commit real secrets.
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values locally.
#
# Claude credential — NOT NEEDED. Orbit classifies and chapterizes by shelling out to
# the `claude` CLI in headless mode (`claude -p`), which uses your existing Claude Code
# subscription. There is NO API key to set and NO pay-as-you-go API credits to buy.
# Just make sure `claude` is installed and on your PATH. (Default model: Claude Sonnet 4.6.)

# X (Twitter) — required to wire the X half of the digest. The read-only X client reads
# these straight from the environment (orbit.py seeds them from this .env at startup).
# They are credentials/identifiers: never logged, never leave your machine. Leave blank
# for a YouTube-only digest.
#   AUTH_TOKEN / CT0 — your X session cookies (used when orbit.config.json sets
#                      "cookie_source": "env"; the X client always reads cookies from env).
#   X_USER_ID        — your numeric X account id (NOT your @handle — the read-only client
#                      has no handle->id lookup). Find it via any "twitter id lookup" tool,
#                      or ask Orbit's setup to resolve it from your @handle.
AUTH_TOKEN=
CT0=
X_USER_ID=

# Email delivery (M5) — required to have the morning digest emailed to you. The digest is
# sent over Gmail SMTP as a summary body + the Tiles HTML page(s) attached. Leave both blank
# to skip email delivery (the digest is still written to disk). Never logged, never leaves
# your machine. The recipient address is NOT here — it lives in orbit.config.json under
# "delivery.email_to".
#   ORBIT_EMAIL_FROM   — the sender Gmail address (also the SMTP login username).
#   GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD — a Gmail *app password* for that account (16 chars). Requires
#                        2-Step Verification enabled; create one at
#                        https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords. NOT your normal password.
ORBIT_EMAIL_FROM=
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=
